==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cogitable
<hw>Cog"i*ta*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>cogitabilis</ets>, fr. <ets>cogitare</ets> to think.]</ety>
<def>Capable of being brought before the mind as a thought or idea;
conceivable; thinkable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Creation is <qex>cogitable</qex> by us only as a putting forth of
divine power.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W. Hamilton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cogitabund</ent>⟦br⟧
